Mike,

All you have to do is to use the special &#39;element&#39;  E to represent the 
charge of ions. For example, OH^- would contain 1 &#39;atom&#39; of element E, 
and H+ would contain -1 atoms of E.
The ion species names can contain &#39;+&#39; or &#39;-&#39; symbols at the end of the 
name, but should not in the middle.

Dave Goodwin


